'''佩吉時間'''（{{lang-en|Page time}}）指的是當[[黑洞|黑洞]]的[[熵|熵]]只剩下初始值的一半，也就是當它的表面積變成只剩一半所需要花費的時間<ref name="don-page-bh-info">Don N. Page. "Information in Black Hole Radiation" ''Physical Review Letters,'' 71, 3743</ref>。有時它亦指[[霍金輻射|黑洞輻射]]的熵含量開始降低的瞬間。佩吉時間是以[[加拿大|加拿大]]籍[[理論物理學|理論物理學]]家[[唐·佩吉_(物理學家)|唐·佩吉]]的姓氏命名的<ref>{{cite web |author=Canada |url=https://newtrail.ualberta.ca/spring2014/bear-country/science-explained |title=Did Hawking say ‘no black holes’? Well, not technically. |publisher=University of Alberta |date=2014-05-12 |accessdate=2015-12-16 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150516083225/http://newtrail.ualberta.ca/spring2014/bear-country/science-explained |archivedate=2015-05-16 |deadurl=yes }}</ref>。

